Problem:
--------
Given an integer array nums, which can have duplicate entries, provide the power set. Duplicate subsets cannot exist in the solution set. Return the answer in any sequence.
Example: 
Input: array[] = [1,2,2]
Output: [ [ ],[1],[1,2],[1,2,2],[2],[2,2] ]
Explanation: We can have subsets ranging from  length 0 to 3. which are listed above. Also the subset [1,2] appears twice but is printed only once as we require only unique subsets.

Solution:
--------
 void findSubsets(int ind, int[] nums,List<Integer> ds,Set<List<Integer>> results) {
    if (ind == nums.length) {
        results.add(new ArrayList<>(ds));
        return;
    }
    // Pick
    ds.add(nums[ind]);
    findSubsets(ind + 1, nums, ds, results);

    // Backtrack
    ds.remove(ds.size() - 1);

    // Not Pick
    findSubsets(ind + 1, nums, ds, results);
}

